    <h2 id="biryani"><u>Veg Biryani</u></h2>
    <img src="https://myfoodstory.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Veg-Biryani-4.jpg"  alt="">
<pre>

  <u><b>Ingredients:</b></u>
        
  <u><b>For the rice:</b></u>
  - 2 cups basmati rice, soaked in water for 30 minutes and drained
  - 4 cups water
  - 2 bay leaves
  - 4 green cardamom pods
  - 4 cloves
  - 1 cinnamon stick
  - Salt to taste
        
  
    <u><b>For the vegetables:</b></u>
        - 2 tablespoons ghee or oil
        - 1 large onion, thinly sliced
        - 2 green chilies, slit
        - 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste
        - 2 medium-sized potatoes, peeled and cubed
        - 1 cup mixed vegetables (carrots, peas, beans, cauliflower, etc.)
        - 1 cup paneer (Indian cottage cheese), cubed
        - 1/2 cup yogurt
        - 1 teaspoon red chili powder
        - 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder
        - 1 teaspoon garam masala
        - Salt to taste
        
    <u><b>For layering:</b></u>
        - 1/4 cup chopped mint leaves
        - 1/4 cup chopped coriander leaves
        - Fried onions (optional)
        - Saffron strands soaked in 2 tablespoons warm milk (optional)
        
    <u><b>Instructions:</b></u>
        
        1. Heat ghee or oil in a large pot. Add sliced onions and sauté until golden brown. Remove half of the fried onions and set aside for layering.
        
        2. To the remaining onions in the pot, add green chilies and ginger-garlic paste. Sauté for a couple of minutes until fragrant.
        
        3. Add potatoes and mixed vegetables. Cook for 5-7 minutes until slightly tender.
        
        4. Add paneer cubes, red chili powder, turmeric powder, garam masala, and salt. Mix well and cook for another 2-3 minutes.
        
        5. In a separate pot, bring water to a boil. Add soaked and drained basmati rice along with bay leaves, cardamom pods, cloves, cinnamon stick, 
        and salt. Cook the rice until it's 70-80% done. Drain the excess water and set the rice aside.
        
        6. Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C).
        
        7. In the pot with the vegetables, spread half of the cooked rice evenly. Sprinkle half of the chopped mint and coriander leaves on top.
        
        8. Spread the yogurt evenly over the rice layer.
        
        9. Add the remaining rice over the yogurt layer and spread it evenly.
        
       10. Sprinkle the remaining chopped mint and coriander leaves over the rice.
        
       11. Spread the reserved fried onions on top. If using saffron, drizzle the saffron-infused milk over the rice.
        
       12. Cover the pot tightly with aluminum foil or a lid and place it in the preheated oven. Bake for 20-25 minutes.
        
       13. Once done, remove the pot from the oven and let it rest for 5-10 minutes before serving.

       Serve the delicious vegetable biryani hot with raita (yogurt sauce) or your favorite chutney. Enjoy your meal!
    </pre>
