    <h2 id="Sandwich"><u>Veg Sandwich</u></h2>
    <img src="https://www.indianhealthyrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/veg-grilled-sandwich-recipe.jpg" >
    <pre>

    <u><b>Ingredients:</b></u>
        
      - 8 slices of bread (whole wheat or white)
      - 1 large tomato, thinly sliced
      - 1 cucumber, thinly sliced
      - 1 small red onion, thinly sliced
      - 1 bell pepper (capsicum), thinly sliced
      - 1 medium-sized carrot, grated or thinly sliced
      - 4 lettuce leaves
      - 1/2 cup mayonnaise or sandwich spread
      - Salt and pepper to taste
      - Optional: sliced cheese, avocado slices, sprouts, pickles, or any other vegetables of your choice
                                - Butter or margarine for spreading on bread slices
        
     <u><b>Instructions:</b></u>
        
        1. Lay out the bread slices on a clean surface.
        
        2. Spread a thin layer of mayonnaise or sandwich spread on each slice of bread.
        
        3. Divide the sliced vegetables evenly among 4 slices of bread. Layer the tomato, cucumber, onion, bell pepper, carrot, lettuce leaves, and any 
        other desired ingredients on the bread.
        
        4. Sprinkle salt and pepper over the vegetable layers according to your taste preferences.
        
        5. If using cheese, place a slice or two on top of the vegetables.
        
        6. Place the remaining slices of bread on top of the vegetable-filled slices to form sandwiches.
        
        7. Lightly spread butter or margarine on the outer sides of the sandwiches.
        
        8. Preheat a sandwich press or a non-stick skillet over medium heat.
        
        9. Place the sandwiches in the sandwich press or skillet and cook until the bread turns golden brown and crispy, and the cheese (if using) melts. 
        If using a skillet, flip the sandwiches halfway through to ensure both sides are evenly toasted.
        
        10. Once the sandwiches are cooked to your liking, remove them from the heat and let them cool for a minute or two.
        
        11. Slice the sandwiches diagonally or into halves, if desired.
        
        12. Serve the veg sandwiches hot with ketchup, mustard, or any dipping sauce of your choice.
        
        Enjoy your delicious and nutritious veg sandwiches!

    </pre>
