    <h2 id="Veg Crispy Momo"><u>Veg Crispy Momo</u></h2>
    <img src="https://5.imimg.com/data5/SELLER/Default/2023/8/332559301/UE/IG/GR/194507844/frozen-kurkurey-momos.jpg" alt="">
    <pre>
        
  <u><b>Ingredients:</b></u>

  <u><b>For the dough:</b></u>
   - 2 cups all-purpose flour
   - Water, as needed
   - Salt, to taste

  <u><b>For the filling:</b></u> 
  - 2 cups mixed vegetables (cabbage, carrots, bell peppers, onions, etc.), finely chopped
  - 2 cloves garlic, minced
  - 1-inch piece of ginger, minced
- 2 green chilies, finely chopped (optional)
- 2 tablespoons soy sauce
- 1 tablespoon chili sauce
- 1 tablespoon vinegar
- 1 teaspoon sesame oil (optional)
- Salt and pepper, to taste
- 2 tablespoons oil for sautéing

<u><b>For frying:</b></u>
- Oil, for deep frying

<u><b>Instructions:</b></u>

1. In a large mixing bowl, combine the all-purpose flour and salt. Slowly add water while kneading the dough until it forms a smooth and firm ball. Cover 
the dough with a damp cloth and let it rest for at least 30 minutes.

2. Meanwhile, prepare the filling. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pan over medium heat. Add minced garlic, ginger, and green chilies (if using). Sauté for 
a minute until fragrant.

3. Add the finely chopped mixed vegetables to the pan. Stir-fry for 5-7 minutes or until the vegetables are tender yet crisp.

4. Add soy sauce, chili sauce, vinegar, sesame oil (if using), salt, and pepper to the vegetable mixture. Mix well to combine all the ingredients. Cook for 
another 2-3 minutes. Remove the filling from heat and let it cool completely.

5. Once the dough has rested, divide it into small lemon-sized balls. Roll out each ball into a thin circle, about 3-4 inches in diameter.

6. Place a spoonful of the cooled vegetable filling in the center of each dough circle.

7. To shape the momos, fold the edges of the dough circle towards the center, pleating and pinching them together to seal the filling inside. You can choose 
any shape you prefer, such as crescent-shaped or round-shaped momos.

8. Heat oil in a deep frying pan or a deep fryer over medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, carefully add the momos to the oil in batches, without overcrowding the pan.

9. Fry the momos until they turn golden brown and crispy, about 4-5 minutes. Remove them from the oil using a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels to remove excess oil.

10. Serve the crispy vegetable momos hot with your favorite dipping sauce, such as chili sauce, soy sauce, or tomato chutney.

Enjoy your delicious Vegetable Crispy Momos as a snack or appetizer!


    </pre>
