    <h2 id="Veg Burger"><u>Veg Burger</u></h2>
    <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSTYnYwVfcdSss1Iay-CgeI_aDUptyuC3BhwA&usqp=CAU" alt="">
<pre>
 <u><b>Ingredients:</b></u>

 <u><b>For the patties:</b></u>
 - 2 cups cooked and drained chickpeas (or canned chickpeas)
 - 1 cup cooked quinoa or brown rice
 - 1 small onion, finely chopped
 - 2 cloves garlic, minced
 - 1 carrot, grated
 - 1/2 cup bread crumbs
 - 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley or cilantro
 - 1 teaspoon ground cumin
 - 1 teaspoon paprika
 - Salt and pepper to taste
- 2 tablespoons olive oil for cooking

<u><b>For assembling the burger:</b></u>
- Burger buns
- Lettuce leaves
- Sliced tomatoes
- Sliced onions
- Sliced cheese (optional)
- Condiments of your choice (ketchup, mustard, mayonnaise, etc.)

<u><b>Instructions:</b></u>

1. In a large mixing bowl, mash the cooked chickpeas using a fork or potato masher until they are partially mashed but still have some texture.

2. Add cooked quinoa or brown rice, finely chopped onion, minced garlic, grated carrot, bread crumbs, chopped parsley or cilantro, ground cumin, paprika, 
salt, and pepper to the mashed chickpeas. Mix everything until well combined.

3. Divide the mixture into equal-sized portions and shape them into patties. If the mixture is too wet, you can add more bread crumbs to bind it together.

4. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Once the oil is hot, add the patties to the skillet (you may need to do this in batches depending on the 
size of your skillet). Cook the patties for 4-5 minutes on each side, or until they are golden brown and crispy.

5. While the patties are cooking, prepare the burger buns by slicing them in half and toasting them lightly if desired.

6. To assemble the burgers, place a lettuce leaf on the bottom half of each burger bun. Top with a cooked veggie patty, sliced tomatoes, onions, and cheese (if using).

7. Spread your favorite condiments on the top half of the burger bun, such as ketchup, mustard, or mayonnaise.

8. Place the top half of the burger bun over the fillings to complete the burger.

9. Serve the veggie burgers immediately, with additional condiments or toppings on the side if desired.

Enjoy your homemade veggie burgers with all the fixings!

</pre>
